[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6791,
        "end_time": 8525,
        "text": "Steel and plastic."
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8525,
        "end_time": 13423,
        "text": "These two materials are essential to so\nmuch of our infrastructure and technology,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 13423,
        "end_time": 17129,
        "text": "and they have a complementary set\nof strengths and weaknesses."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 17129,
        "end_time": 18900,
        "text": "Steel is strong and hard,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 18900,
        "end_time": 21249,
        "text": "but difficult to shape intricately."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 21249,
        "end_time": 23885,
        "text": "While plastic can take on \njust about any form,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 23885,
        "end_time": 26072,
        "text": "it&#39;s weak and soft."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 26072,
        "end_time": 28424,
        "text": "So wouldn&#39;t it be nice if there\nwere one material"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 28424,
        "end_time": 30616,
        "text": "as strong as the strongest steel"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 30616,
        "end_time": 33507,
        "text": "and as shapeable as plastic?"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 33507,
        "end_time": 36092,
        "text": "Well, a lot of scientists \nand technologists"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 36092,
        "end_time": 41039,
        "text": "are getting excited about a relatively\nrecent invention called metallic glass"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 41039,
        "end_time": 44290,
        "text": "with both of those properties, and more."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 44290,
        "end_time": 47509,
        "text": "Metallic glasses look shiny and opaque,\nlike metals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 47509,
        "end_time": 51120,
        "text": "and also like metals,\nthey conduct heat and electricity."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 51120,
        "end_time": 53500,
        "text": "But they&#39;re way stronger than most metals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 53500,
        "end_time": 56101,
        "text": "which means they can withstand\na lot of force"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 56101,
        "end_time": 58449,
        "text": "without getting bent or dented,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 58449,
        "end_time": 60193,
        "text": "making ultrasharp scalpels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 60193,
        "end_time": 62253,
        "text": "and ultrastrong electronics cases,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 62253,
        "end_time": 63089,
        "text": "hinges,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 63089,
        "end_time": 64132,
        "text": "screws;"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 64132,
        "end_time": 65632,
        "text": "the list goes on."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 65632,
        "end_time": 68019,
        "text": "Metallic glasses also \nhave an incredible ability"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 68019,
        "end_time": 70755,
        "text": "to store and release elastic energy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 70755,
        "end_time": 73133,
        "text": "which makes them perfect \nfor sports equipment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 73133,
        "end_time": 74258,
        "text": "like tennis racquets,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 74258,
        "end_time": 75320,
        "text": "golf clubs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 75320,
        "end_time": 76700,
        "text": "and skis."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 76700,
        "end_time": 78219,
        "text": "They&#39;re resistant to corrosion,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 78219,
        "end_time": 82375,
        "text": "and can be cast into complex shapes\nwith mirror-like surfaces"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 82375,
        "end_time": 84499,
        "text": "in a single molding step."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 84499,
        "end_time": 86812,
        "text": "Despite their strength \nat room temperature,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 86812,
        "end_time": 89202,
        "text": "if you go up a few hundred \ndegrees Celsius,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 89202,
        "end_time": 91062,
        "text": "they soften significantly,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 91062,
        "end_time": 94474,
        "text": "and can be deformed into\nany shape you like."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 94474,
        "end_time": 95832,
        "text": "Cool them back down,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 95832,
        "end_time": 98278,
        "text": "and they regain the strength."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 98278,
        "end_time": 101206,
        "text": "So where do all of these wondrous\nattributes come from?"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 101206,
        "end_time": 105519,
        "text": "In essence, they have to do with\nmetallic glass&#39; unique atomic structure."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 105519,
        "end_time": 108154,
        "text": "Most metals are crystalline as solids."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 108154,
        "end_time": 112278,
        "text": "That means that if you zoomed in\nclose enough to see the individual atoms,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 112278,
        "end_time": 116304,
        "text": "they&#39;d be neatly lined up\nin an orderly, repeating pattern"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 116304,
        "end_time": 118587,
        "text": "that extends throughout \nthe whole material."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 118587,
        "end_time": 119871,
        "text": "Ice is crystalline,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 119871,
        "end_time": 121124,
        "text": "and so are diamonds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 121124,
        "end_time": 122219,
        "text": "and salt."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 122219,
        "end_time": 124603,
        "text": "If you heat these materials up enough\nand melt them,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 124603,
        "end_time": 127985,
        "text": "the atoms can jiggle freely\nand move randomly,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 127985,
        "end_time": 129590,
        "text": "but when you cool them back down,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 129590,
        "end_time": 131427,
        "text": "the atoms reorganize themselves,"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 131427,
        "end_time": 133841,
        "text": "reestablishing the crystal."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 133841,
        "end_time": 137219,
        "text": "But what if you could cool \na molten metal so fast"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 137219,
        "end_time": 140055,
        "text": "that the atoms couldn&#39;t \nfind their places again,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 140055,
        "end_time": 141914,
        "text": "so that the material was solid,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 141914,
        "end_time": 146356,
        "text": "but with the chaotic, amorphous internal\nstructure of a liquid?"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 146356,
        "end_time": 148096,
        "text": "That&#39;s metallic glass."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 148096,
        "end_time": 151579,
        "text": "This structure has the added benefit\nof lacking the grain boundaries"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 151579,
        "end_time": 153472,
        "text": "that most metals have."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 153472,
        "end_time": 156884,
        "text": "Those are weak spots where the material\nis more susceptible to scratches"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 156884,
        "end_time": 158783,
        "text": "or corrosion."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 158783,
        "end_time": 163394,
        "text": "The first metallic glass was made\nin 1960 from gold and silicon."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 163394,
        "end_time": 164837,
        "text": "It wasn&#39;t easy to make."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 164837,
        "end_time": 167505,
        "text": "Because metal atoms \ncrystallize so rapidly,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 167505,
        "end_time": 171405,
        "text": "scientists had to cool the alloy down\nincredibly fast,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 171405,
        "end_time": 174527,
        "text": "a million degrees Kelvin per second,"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 174527,
        "end_time": 177456,
        "text": "by shooting tiny droplets\nat cold copper plates,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 177456,
        "end_time": 180317,
        "text": "or spinning ultrathin ribbons."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 180317,
        "end_time": 185440,
        "text": "At that time, metallic glasses could\nonly be tens or hundreds of microns thick,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 185440,
        "end_time": 188657,
        "text": "which was too thin \nfor most practical applications."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 188657,
        "end_time": 190715,
        "text": "But since then, \nscientists have figured out"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 190715,
        "end_time": 194318,
        "text": "that if you blend several metals\nthat mix with each other freely,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 194318,
        "end_time": 196899,
        "text": "but can&#39;t easily crystallize together,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 196899,
        "end_time": 199701,
        "text": "usually because they have very different\natomic sizes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 199701,
        "end_time": 202945,
        "text": "the mixture crystallizes much more slowly."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 202945,
        "end_time": 206034,
        "text": "That means you don&#39;t have to cool\nit down as fast,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 206034,
        "end_time": 207616,
        "text": "so the material can be thicker,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 207616,
        "end_time": 210092,
        "text": "centimeters instead of micrometers."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 210092,
        "end_time": 214375,
        "text": "These materials are called bulk\nmetallic glasses, or BMGs."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 214375,
        "end_time": 217042,
        "text": "Now there are hundreds of different BMGs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 217042,
        "end_time": 220109,
        "text": "so why aren&#39;t all of our bridges\nand cars made out of them?"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 220109,
        "end_time": 224349,
        "text": "Many of the BMGs currently available\nare made from expensive metals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 224349,
        "end_time": 226537,
        "text": "like palladium and zirconium,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 226537,
        "end_time": 228022,
        "text": "and they have to be really pure"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 228022,
        "end_time": 231374,
        "text": "because any impurities \ncan cause crystallization."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 231374,
        "end_time": 236386,
        "text": "So a BMG skyscraper or space shuttle\nwould be astronomically expensive."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 236386,
        "end_time": 237776,
        "text": "And despite their strength,"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 237776,
        "end_time": 242089,
        "text": "they&#39;re not yet tough enough\nfor load-bearing applications."
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 242089,
        "end_time": 245082,
        "text": "When the stresses get high,\nthey can fracture without warning,"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 245082,
        "end_time": 248206,
        "text": "which isn&#39;t ideal for, say, a bridge."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 248206,
        "end_time": 252065,
        "text": "But when engineers figure out\nhow to make BMGs from cheaper metals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 252065,
        "end_time": 254058,
        "text": "and how to make them even tougher,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 254058,
        "end_time": 255736,
        "text": "for these super materials,"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 255736,
        "end_time": 257309,
        "text": "the sky&#39;s the limit."
    }
]